Business Brief -- Computer Associates:
   Software Firm's Stock Rises
   On News of 3rd-Period Net
In response, Computer Associates shares rose $3.25 and
were quoted at $15.125 a share in late New York Stock
Exchange trading yesterday.
   The company cited strength in manufacturing and warehouse
software for International Business Machines Corp.'s AS/400
midrange computer and new database software for personal
computers.
   In an interview, Charles B. Wang, chairman, said he
expects fourth-quarter earnings will exceed the year-earlier
35 cents a share.
   In the first nine months, net rose 14% to $108.7 million,
or 61 cents a share, from $95 million, or 51 cents a share.
Revenue rose 9.5% to $1.04 billion.